<script data-name="featured-video-mapped-to-wiki">
(function () {
// we can't use mw.config here because it's too early so we need to pass this data in different way
var videoDetails = {
mediaId: "K21eFFRc",
impressionsPerSession: 4,
isDedicatedForArticle: false,
};
var hasVideoOnPage = null;
var videoBridgeCountries = ["US","GB","CA","AU","DE","SG","MY","VN","ID","PH","TH","ES","FR","AR","CL","MX","BR"];

function getCookieValue(cookieName) {
var cookieSplit = ('; ' + document.cookie).split('; ' + cookieName + '=');
return cookieSplit.length === 2 ? cookieSplit.pop().split(';').shift() : null;
}

function hasMaxedOutPlayerImpressionsInWiki() {
var impressionsSoFar = Number(getCookieValue('playerImpressionsInWiki')) || 0;
var allowedImpressions = Number(videoDetails.impressionsPerSession);

if (!hasSeenTheVideoInCurrentSession()) {
return false;
}

if (allowedImpressions === 0) {
return true;
}

return impressionsSoFar >= allowedImpressions;
}

function hasSeenTheVideoInCurrentSession() {
var currentSession = getCookieValue('wikia_session_id');
var videoSeenInSession = getCookieValue('featuredVideoSeenInSession');

return currentSession && videoSeenInSession && currentSession === videoSeenInSession;
}

function getCountryCode() {
try {
return JSON.parse(decodeURIComponent(getCookieValue('Geo'))).country.toLowerCase();
} catch {
return null;
}
}

function isVideoBridgeAllowedForCountry() {
var countryCode = getCountryCode();
var allowedCountries = videoBridgeCountries.map(function (allowedCountryCode) {
return allowedCountryCode.toLowerCase();
});

return countryCode && allowedCountries.indexOf(countryCode) !== -1;
}

window.canPlayVideo = function () {
if (hasVideoOnPage === null) {
hasVideoOnPage = videoDetails.mediaId && (
videoDetails.isDedicatedForArticle ||
(!hasMaxedOutPlayerImpressionsInWiki() && isVideoBridgeAllowedForCountry())
);
}

return hasVideoOnPage;
};

if (!window.canPlayVideo()) {
document.body.classList.add('no-featured-video');
} else {
document.body.classList.add('has-featured-video');
}
})();
</script>

<p>There are 413 villagers in <i><a href="/wiki/Animal_Crossing:_New_Horizons" title="Animal Crossing: New Horizons">New Horizons</a></i>, excluding <a href="/wiki/Special_characters" class="mw-redirect" title="Special characters">special characters</a>. All villagers present in <i><a href="/wiki/Animal_Crossing:_New_Leaf" title="Animal Crossing: New Leaf">New Leaf</a></i> and most from <i><a href="/wiki/Welcome_amiibo" title="Welcome amiibo">Welcome amiibo</a></i> make a return, while 16 new villagers are added: <a href="/wiki/Audie" title="Audie">Audie</a> (<a href="/wiki/Peppy" title="Peppy">peppy</a> <a href="/wiki/Wolf" title="Wolf">wolf</a>), <a href="/wiki/Cyd" title="Cyd">Cyd</a> (<a href="/wiki/Cranky" title="Cranky">cranky</a> <a href="/wiki/Elephant" title="Elephant">elephant</a>), <a href="/wiki/Dom" title="Dom">Dom</a> (<a href="/wiki/Jock" title="Jock">jock</a> <a href="/wiki/Sheep" title="Sheep">sheep</a>), <a href="/wiki/Judy" title="Judy">Judy</a> (<a href="/wiki/Snooty" title="Snooty">snooty</a> <a href="/wiki/Cub" title="Cub">cub</a>), <a href="/wiki/Megan" title="Megan">Megan</a> (<a href="/wiki/Normal" title="Normal">normal</a> <a href="/wiki/Bear" title="Bear">bear</a>), <a href="/wiki/Raymond" title="Raymond">Raymond</a> (<a href="/wiki/Smug" title="Smug">smug</a> <a href="/wiki/Cat" title="Cat">cat</a>), <a href="/wiki/Reneigh" title="Reneigh">Reneigh</a> (<a href="/wiki/Sisterly" title="Sisterly">sisterly</a> <a href="/wiki/Horse" title="Horse">horse</a>), <a href="/wiki/Sherb" title="Sherb">Sherb</a> (<a href="/wiki/Lazy" title="Lazy">lazy</a> <a href="/wiki/Goat" title="Goat">goat</a>), <a href="/wiki/Sasha" title="Sasha">Sasha</a> (<a href="/wiki/Lazy" title="Lazy">lazy</a> <a href="/wiki/Rabbit" title="Rabbit">rabbit</a>), <a href="/wiki/Ione" title="Ione">Ione</a> (<a href="/wiki/Normal" title="Normal">normal</a> <a href="/wiki/Squirrel" title="Squirrel">squirrel</a>), <a href="/wiki/Tiansheng" title="Tiansheng">Tiansheng</a> (<a href="/wiki/Jock" title="Jock">jock</a> <a href="/wiki/Monkey" title="Monkey">monkey</a>), <a href="/wiki/Shino" title="Shino">Shino</a> (<a href="/wiki/Peppy" title="Peppy">peppy</a> <a href="/wiki/Deer" title="Deer">deer</a>), <a href="/wiki/Marlo" title="Marlo">Marlo</a> (<a href="/wiki/Cranky" title="Cranky">cranky</a> <a href="/wiki/Hamster" title="Hamster">hamster</a>), <a href="/wiki/Petri" title="Petri">Petri</a> (<a href="/wiki/Snooty" title="Snooty">snooty</a> <a href="/wiki/Mouse" title="Mouse">mouse</a>), <a href="/wiki/Cephalobot" title="Cephalobot">Cephalobot</a> (<a href="/wiki/Smug" title="Smug">smug</a> <a href="/wiki/Octopus_(villager)" title="Octopus (villager)">octopus</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Quinn" title="Quinn">Quinn</a> (<a href="/wiki/Sisterly" title="Sisterly">sisterly</a> <a href="/wiki/Eagle" title="Eagle">eagle</a>). In addition, eight villagers from the original <i>Animal Crossing</i> games return for the first time in nearly 20 years.
</p>
